It all starts with CSV file...




1. Download the CSV file from the Red Icon  . Click on it and save the file in your computer.

2. On Power Bi Desktop, go to the Home tab and click on the Get Data icon from the Data menu.

3. Select the Text/CSV option.

4. Find and select the file in your computer and double click on it to open it.

5. A window with a preview of the data will appear. Click on Load.

6. When you see that the table has been loaded. Click on the name of the name of the table and rename it to FactTable.



https://docs.microsoft.com/en-us/power-bi/connect-data/desktop-connect-csv
